                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d862">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">396.1 GE/7–754: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">United States Delegation</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential<lb/>priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-07-07T10:00:00+01:00"
                            >July 7, 1954—10 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Secto1">Secto</gloss> 564. Re <gloss target="#t_Secto1"
                        >Secto</gloss> 561.<note n="1" xml:id="d862fn1">Dated July 6, <ref
                            target="#pg_1289">p. 1289</ref>.</note> At next session July 9, I plan
                    to make short statement on question of introduction of arms and military
                    personnel into Laos and Cambodia after cessation of hostilities. Unless
                    instructed to contrary, I will reiterate points made by Under Secretary at
                    session of June 19, and support positions taken by Cambodian and Laotian
                    delegates on July 8.<note n="2" xml:id="d862fn2">In telegram <gloss
                            target="#t_Tosec1">Tosec</gloss> 520, July 7, the Department of State
                        replied that it concurred with Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_JUA1"
                            >Johnson</persName>‘s decision. (396.1 GE/7–754)</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_JUA1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
